## Routing

API routes are in `config/routes/api.rb`, drawn as `namespace :api, defaults: { format: :json }`.

## Base controller

All API controllers inherit `API::BaseController`:
- Auth: `HTTP_X_ACCESS_TOKEN` header → `AccessToken` → `current_user`
- Call `authenticate_user!` (raises `UnauthorizedError`) for protected endpoints
- JSON rendering via `API::RenderingHelper`
- Global `rescue_from` for 404, 422, 500

## Conventions

- Use `param: :uuid` for article resources
- Locale forced to `:en` in API (`with_locale`)
- Log last request metadata on access tokens in `after_action`

## Avoid

- Returning full article `content` without authorization (see existing `articles#show` behavior)
- HTML/session auth patterns from `ApplicationController` in API controllers
